applicationInfo.description:
HNEtConnect is an online directory that lists doctors, clinics, and other

medical facilities to allow customers to find the right type of care at the

right locations. It contains doctors personal information, work addresses,

medical certifications, and types of services that the doctors and clinics

offer. Doctors are given credentials and can update the information in their

profile.

HNetPay is a web portal used by many customers to support the

management of secure payments and billing. The portal, hosted at Health

Network products sites, accepts various forms of payments and interacts

with credit card processing organizations.

HNextExchange is the primary source of revenue. This service handles

secure electronic medical messages that originate from its customers, such

as large hospitals, which are then routed to receiving customers such as

clinics.

**ASSETS:**

| System                                      | Function                                                                                                  | Potential Failure                                                                      | Consequences on other systems                                                                                                                |
| ------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Epic EHR Windows Server                     | Transmits patient data and provides assistance with clinical workflow.                                    | Malware and power outages                                                              | Cause inability to access clinical systems used in daily workflow                                                                            |
| Radiology PACS System                       | For storing and retrieving images from processes such as MRIS and X-rays                                  | Malware and power outages                                                              | Could cause radiology to not be able to upload images to databases or retrieve images from databases                                         |
| Labratory Information System                | Lab orders and processing                                                                                 | malware and power outages                                                              | Halt processing lab orders                                                                                                                   |
| Financial Systems                           | Patient billing and payment processing. Stores PII DSS                                                    | Patient billing and payment processing                                                 | Halt posting bills and fulfillment of payments                                                                                               |
| CrowdStrike Falcon (EDR) Protection         | Endpoint protection is implemented on all endpoints (847)                                                 | Power outages, network  connectivity issues, and threat actor                          | Cause endpoint devices detection to be taken offline along with endpoints no longer being protected                                          |
| Palo alto PA-33330 Firewalls                | Firewalls are implemented on all network segments \~24                                                    | Power outage/ Turned off by threat actor                                               | Inability to ensure malicious traffic does not reach web application                                                                         |
| Active Directory 2019 with Azure AD Connect | Service used in authentication and access controls.                                                       | Turned off by threat actor/ Power outage                                               | Inability to authenticate users preventing access to various web applications                                                                |
| Rapid7 (Vulnerability Scanner)              | Scans multiple IT assets for vulnerabilities                                                              | Turned off by threat actor/ power outage                                               | Inability to scan vulnerabilities on multiple systems                                                                                        |
| Load balancers                              | Distributes traffic across various web applications like MyChart, HNetConnect, HNetPay, and HNetExchange  | Power outages, threat actors                                                           | Could cause disruptions in various web applications as traffic is no longer distributed                                                      |
| 23 Servers                                  | Servers are used for hosting web applications, databases, and authentication systems.                     | Power outages/ Threat actor                                                            | Could cause applications hosted on servers/ information to be inaccessible                                                                   |
| Log servers                                 | Logs transactions from various web applications                                                           | Disabled by threat actor/ data loss/ power outages                                     | Could prevent security from being able to monitor possible malicious activity                                                                |
| Databases                                   | Stores information or various web applications                                                            | Data loss/ power outages/ Disabled by threat actor                                     | Inability to retrieve payments, mail, and update doctor information                                                                          |
| Splunk                                      | Also SOC to view centralized logs from various web applications                                           | Threat actor/ Power Outage                                                             | Inability to view logs possibly leading to threat actors evading detection                                                                   |
| Patient Health Information                  | Used by web applications to provide patient info for hospitals and clinics communicating with one another | Threat actor/ Power Outage                                                             | Loss of availability, integrity, or confidentiality of data                                                                                  |
| Personally Identifiable Information         | Used by web applications to display doctor information or patient information                             | Threat actor/ Power Outage                                                             | Loss of availability, integrity, or confidentiality of data                                                                                  |
| Financial Information                       | used by HNETPay to provide billing information                                                            | Threat actor/ Power Outage                                                             | Loss of availability, integrity, or confidentiality of data                                                                                  |
| West Lafayette Facility                     | The Main Headquarters used by employees to  assist in managing HealthNetwork products                     | The Main Headquarters used by employees to  assist in managing HealthNetwork products  | Possible outages of multiple products, inability to manage web applications, loss of life if facility does not have proper saftey guidelines |
| Portland, Oregon Facility                   | Used by employees to  assist in managing HealthNetwork products                                           | Threat actor/ Power Outage/Natural Disaster                                            | Threat actor/ Power Outage/Natural Disaster                                                                                                  |
| Threat actor/ Power Outage/Natural Disaster | Used by employees to  assist in managing HealthNetwork products                                           | Threat actor/ Power Outage/Natural Disaster                                            | Possible outages of multiple products, inability to manage web applications, loss of life if facility does not have proper saftey guidelines |
applicationInfo.name: HNetConnect, HNetPay, HNetExchange

threats.statement: An external threat actor with a bot net that is able to request access to one of health network's web applications can preform a DDOS attack, which leads to the web application server not being able to respond to threats, resulting in reduced availability of web application server
threats.prerequisites: with a bot net that is able to request access to one of health network's web applications
threats.threatImpact: the web application server not being able to respond to threats
